# Workflow

Read [.notebook/README.md](../../.notebook/README.md) and [.notebook/workflow.md](../../.notebook/workflow.md) before plan, design, or backlog work.

## Folder order

`00_references` → `01` → `02` → `03` → `backlogs/` (ready) → `06_design` → code → `05_reports`

Do not store raw intake in the repo.

## Skill routing

Invoke matching skills from `.cursor/skills/`:

| Situation | Skill |
|-----------|-------|
| Intent unclear (who/why/success) | `interview-me` |
| Many options / MVP | `idea-refine` |
| Raw intake → one draft task | `analyze-intake-to-task` |
| Catalog / scope impact (01–03) | `spec-driven-development` |
| Split tasks, INVEST, status `ready` | `planning-and-task-breakdown` |
| Basic design (M+ scope) | `basic-design` |
| Detail design (before develop) | `detail-design` |
| Task done → PM/client report | `report-writer` |

## Pipeline

```
INTAKE → define → plan → ready → design → develop → test → report
```

Do not set task status `ready` without INVEST and human approval.  
Do not implement M+ work without design links in task **Design** section.

